    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-11-18T06:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-11-18T06:00:00-05:00" n="265"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d265">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/25812: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Spain</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hayes</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Madrid</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-11-18T12:00:00+01:00"
                            >November 18, 1942—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received 8 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1823. My 1819, November 17, 8 p.m.,<note n="67" xml:id="d265fn67">Not
                        printed.</note> and 1822, November 18. It is perhaps superfluous for me to
                    point out that the partial mobilization decree with its preamble expressing
                    Spain’s determination to defend its integrity and sovereignty and to keep out of
                    the war is a very favorable development from our point of view.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hayes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
